{{Infobox Magazine | title = Destiny | image_file = [[File:Khanyi_Dhlomo,_October_2008_cover_of_Destiny_Magazine.jpg]] | image_caption = [[Khanyi Dhlomo]] on the 1st anniversary edition of Destiny Magazine | publisher = Media24 | editor = {{Plainlist| *Khanyi Dhlomo (Founding Editor) *Ingrid Wood}} | frequency = Monthly | circulation = 31 091<ref name=circulation>{{cite web|title=Destiny Magazine|url=http://www.magazines.co.za/magazine/destiny_magazine_1.html|work=Magazines TM|accessdate=5 May 2014}}</ref> | category = [[Business magazine|Business]], [[Fashion magazine|fashion]] , [[Lifestyle magazine|lifestyle]] | company = Ndalo Media | firstdate = October 8, 2007 | country = [[South Africa]] | language = | website = {{URL|http://www.destinyconnect.com/}} }}
'''''Destiny''''' is a monthly high-end business, lifestyle and fashion magazine for women. It is published in [[South African]] by Ndalo Media.
==History== Ndalo Media is a print and digital media company that owns and publishes Destiny and Destiny Man magazines. It was founded by Khanyi Dhlomo in partnership with [[Media24]] (under [[Naspers]]) and published the first issue of Destiny in October 2007.
==Target audience== Destiny is aimed at women who either aspire to be or are actively engaged in business and who are 25–55 years old. The magazine combines business news (South African and global) with fashion, beauty, lifestyle, entertainment, health, travel and inspirational content.<ref name=about>{{cite web|title=About Destiny|url=http://www.destinyconnect.com/about-us/|work=Destiny Connect|publisher=Ndalo Media|accessdate=5 May 2014}}</ref>
==Destiny Man== Destiny Man is an alternate-monthly publication aimed at accomplished, stylish, affluent and self-assured South African men. It is the brother publication to Destiny. Destiny Man launched its first issue in July 2009, followed by its online extension in the same month.
